Docs.summary: Line Head/End Style. When the object is serialized out as xml, its qualified name is a:headEnd.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)] `headEnd (Line Head/End Style)` This element specifies decorations which can be added to the head of a line. [*Example*: 206dbf80-a378-4270-b9b7-e4a4280ec7c1 *end exmaple*] |Parent Elements| |---------------------| |ln (§20.1.2.2.24); lnB (§21.1.3.5); lnBlToTr (§21.1.3.6); lnL (§21.1.3.7); lnR (§21.1.3.8); lnT (§21.1.3.9); lnTlToBr (§21.1.3.10); uLn (§21.1.2.3.14)| |Attributes|Description| |----------------|-----------------| |len (Length of Head/End)|Specifies the line end length in relation to the line width.

The possible values for this attribute are defined by the *ST_LineEndLength* simple type (§20.1.10.32).| |type (Line Head/End Type)|Specifies the line end decoration, such as a triangle or arrowhead.

The possible values for this attribute are defined by the *ST_LineEndType* simple type (§20.1.10.33).| |w (Width of Head/End)|Specifies the line end width in relation to the line width.

The possible values for this attribute are defined by the *ST_LineEndWidth* simple type (§20.1.10.34).| [*Note*: The W3C XML Schema definition of this element’s content model (CT_LineEndProperties) is located in §A.4.1. *end note*] [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlcopyrightiso.md)]
